subSubSection.paragraph:
(
Figures 5–7
)

Chaetiger 1 with only a few chaetae in both rami, especially on the notopodium, shorter than chaetae on succeeding chaetigers. Postchaetal lamellae oval on both rami, much smaller than lamellae on succeeding chaetigers (
Fig. 7A
). Prechaetal lamellae absent.

Hooks in notopodia starting from chaetigers 20–23, up to five per fascicle, accompanied by 1–5 short non-limbate capillaries (
Fig. 7H
). Hooks in neuropodia starting from chaetigers 13–16, up to nine per fascicle, accompanied by 3–7 non-limbate capillaries. All hooks tridentate, with a single pair of teeth arranged side by side above main tooth (
Figs 6C
, 
7I
). Small secondary hood present (
Fig. 7I
). Sabre chaetae absent throughout.

Up to 11 pairs of smooth and cirriform branchiae, tapered distally. Branchiae starting from chaetiger 2, up to four times longer than notopodial lamellae, gradually reduced in length towards last branchial pair. Branchiae densely ciliated throughout its length, completely free from notopodial postchaetal lamellae (
Fig. 7J
).

Pygidium bearing one long dorsal cirrus and two short ventral cirri (
Fig. 7K
).
